
Ubuntu 16.4

1. copy the startup.sh file to /tmp on the remote machine.
2. chmod +x on /tmp/startup.sh
3. run the file: cd tmp && ./startup.sh


On-premise:

Prerequisites:

1. Docker must be installed on the offline machine.


On premise install:

1. Run the onpremise_build.sh script on a machine which has internet connection.
2. Copy the two generated tar files to the machine which has no access to the internet.
3. Run the onpremise_load.sh script (The files should reside in the same folder as the script)
4. Run docker-compose up
